## âš™ï¸ Stepwise Execution Plan

### **Stage 1 â€” Initialization**
- [ ] Verify domain ownership (`perezfashion.com`)
- [ ] Clone repo into `~/perez_fashion`
- [ ] Run `npm install` or `docker compose up -d --build`
- [ ] Confirm local site works: `http://localhost:3000`

### **Stage 2 â€” Branding & Content**
- [ ] Update metadata (Business name, email, hours)
- [ ] Insert logo and photos in `/public/`
- [ ] Replace Formspree endpoint with real ID
- [ ] Add business contact info and WhatsApp link

### **Stage 3 â€” Deployment**
- [ ] Build static assets: `npm run build`
- [ ] Run with Docker Compose or systemd service
- [ ] Verify Nginx or Cloudflare Tunnel routing to `https://perezfashion.com`

### **Stage 4 â€” SEO & Analytics**
- [ ] Validate `robots.ts` and `sitemap.ts`
- [ ] Add LocalBusiness JSON-LD metadata
- [ ] Register Google Business Profile
- [ ] Add analytics script (Plausible or Google Analytics)

### **Stage 5 â€” Marketing Integration**
- [ ] Link Instagram & Facebook pages
- [ ] Add call-to-action buttons on Home & Consulting pages
- [ ] Create blog or tips section for SEO (optional)
- [ ] Encourage customer reviews on Google & social media

---

## ðŸ§  AI Agent Objectives

**Agent name:** `TailorSite-Agent`

### **Capabilities**
- Modify project files under `~/perez_fashion`
- Generate new `.tsx` pages or components on request
- Execute safe shell commands (install, build, docker compose)
- Propose and apply SEO improvements
- Draft content for services, consulting, and posts

### **Guardrails**
- Never run destructive commands without confirmation
- Keep secrets (e.g., API keys) in `.env`
- Log file changes before writing
- Respect `robots.txt` and domain safety

